Blocks.childText: PRAYER TO GOD 259 THY WILL BE DONE Concluded CHORUS D. S. Thy will be done," 'Thy will be done Thy will be done," Thy will be done From " The Corona" By per. of the Author 565 2 Though dark my path, and sad my lot, 4 Renew my will from day to day; Let me be still and murmur not, Blend it with Thine, and take away Or breathe the prayer divinely taught, All that now makes it hard to say "Thy will be done! "Thy will be done!" 3 If Thou shouldst call me to resign 5 Then, when on earth I breathe no more What most I prize,-it ne'er was mine : The prayer oft mixed with tears before, I only yield Thee what is Thine; I'll sing upon a happier shore, 'Thy will be done! Thy will be done!' Charlotte Elliott HEAVENLY FATHER, HEAR ME J. F. KING Heaven- ly Fa - ther, heaven ly Fa ther, Hear me as I come to Thee 9 Fine See me kneel - ing, hum bly plead - ing That Thou ev er stay by me. D. S. Heaven-ly Fa ther, heaven- Fa ther, Give to me Thy gra cious smile. ID. S. In Thy pres ence, joy and glad - ness Is my por tion all the while, Words and Music Copyright, 1895, by Christian Pub. Co. 566 2 Heavenly Father, heavenly Father, 3 Heavenly Father, heavenly Father, I rejoice to stay by Thee : See, I yield my life to Thee. Thou SO loving ; always proving Stoop and raise me, while I praise Thee Thy great tenderness to me. For Thy mercy rich and free. Oh, the richness, oh, the sweetness, Now, while living and receiving Of communion close with Thee. Only good, dear Lord, from Thee, Heavenly Father, heavenly Father, Help me, Father, help me ever Keep me Thine eternally. Loving service bring to Thee. Anna D. Bradley
